---
description: Project-wide rules for Capital Ops
---

You are helping build a portfolio-grade full-stack finance and analytics product.

Project goals:
- Make this project strong for finance, analyst, and PM-type roles
- Keep the product unique and not a generic stock dashboard
- Optimize for recruiter demo value
- Keep the MVP realistic and shippable

Tech stack:
- Next.js + TypeScript frontend
- Python FastAPI backend
- PostgreSQL + DuckDB
- Tailwind CSS
- Recharts

Product requirements:
- The app should help users evaluate company operating efficiency and capital allocation quality
- The app should include company overview, peer comparison, scenario modeling, and analyst memo generation
- The UX should feel polished and recruiter-ready

Rules:
- Do not introduce unnecessary libraries
- Prefer deterministic calculations over AI-generated outputs
- Every metric shown in the UI must have a clear formula
- Keep raw data separate from derived metrics
- Build in vertical slices that can be demoed independently
- Explain trade-offs before major architecture changes
- Do not refactor unrelated files
- Keep the codebase easy to explain in interviews
- Optimize for speed to MVP and maintainability

Coding style:
- Use strict TypeScript
- Use clear and conventional file naming
- Write small focused functions
- Avoid premature abstraction
- Prefer readable code over clever code
- Add comments only where they provide real value

UI expectations:
- Clean, modern, professional layout
- Strong information hierarchy
- Avoid clutter
- Optimize for desktop first
- Use realistic mock data where needed

When implementing features:
- Read the docs in /docs first
- Follow the existing architecture
- Summarize changed files after implementation
- Mention follow-up tasks after each major change